%N A000445 Latest possible occurrence of the first consecutive pair of n-th power residues, modulo any prime.
%C A000445 The paper by Adolf Hildebrand proves that a(n) is finite for all n. - _Christopher E. Thompson_, Dec 05 2019
%C A000445 _Don Reble_ has reported computations proving that 1499876 <= a(8) <= 1508324, which improves on the references below. Note also that it shows a(8) < a(7). - _Christopher E. Thompson_, Jan 14 2020
